        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 9 at 3:55AM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 355 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Burlington, or 7 miles northwest of Minot, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Minot, Minot Air Force Base, and Burlington.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
